HEADWORD: kurakkan
<hw>kurakkan</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An East Indian cereal grass
(<spn>Eleusine coracana</spn>) whose seed yield a somewhat bitter flour,
a staple in the Orient.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> finger millet, ragi, ragee, African millet, coracan,
corakan, <spn>Eleusine coracana</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

